<div class="content"><p>The Internet Information Services (IIS) Inetinfo Remote
Protocol provides functions that allow remote administration and statistics
gathering from an <a href="ce912734-75c3-403c-8816-38e34e24df2f#gt_d9a0cf88-f6d7-4c52-a9fc-4ce5a7cb7260" data-linktype="relative-path">Internet
protocol server</a> such as a server implementing the HTTP or FTP protocol. The
protocol provides methods for gathering statistical data on users, sites,
requests, and performance. For more information about HTTP and securing HTTP
connections, see <a href="https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=90310" data-linktype="external">[RFC2068]</a>
and <a href="https://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=90383" data-linktype="external">[RFC2818]</a>.</p><p>The server does not maintain client state information.
Although some client call sequences might be logically related, the protocol
operation is stateless.</p></div>